{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:matthew.22",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "matthew",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Matthew 22 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:1",
      "text": "And Jesus answering, spoke again in parables to them, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:2",
      "text": "The kingdom of heaven is likened to a king who made a marriage for his son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:3",
      "text": "And he sent his servants to call them that were invited to the marriage: and they would not come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:4",
      "text": "Again he sent other servants, saying: Tell them that were invited, Behold, I have prepared my dinner: my beeves and fatlings are killed, and all things are ready. Come ye to the marriage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:5",
      "text": "But they neglected and went their ways, one to his farm and another to his merchandise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:6",
      "text": "And the rest laid hands on his servants and, having treated them contumeliously, put them to death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:7",
      "text": "But when the king had heard of it, he was angry: and sending his armies, he destroyed those murderers and burnt their city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:8",
      "text": "Then he saith to his servants: The marriage indeed is ready; but they that were invited were not worthy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:9",
      "text": "Go ye therefore into the highways; and as many as you shall find, call to the marriage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:10",
      "text": "And his servants going forth into the ways, gathered together all that they found, both bad and good: and the marriage was filled with guests.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:11",
      "text": "And the king went in to see the guests: and he saw there a man who had not on a wedding garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:12",
      "text": "And he saith to him: Friend, how camest thou in hither not having on a wedding garment? But he was silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:13",
      "text": "Then the king said to the waiters: Bind his hands and feet, and cast him into the exterior darkness. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:14",
      "text": "For many are called, but few are chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:15",
      "text": "Then the Pharisees going, consulted among themselves how to insnare him in his speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:16",
      "text": "And they sent to him their disciples with the Herodians, saying: Master, we know that thou art a true speaker and teachest the way of God in truth. Neither carest thou for any man: for thou dost not regard the person of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:17",
      "text": "Tell us therefore what dost thou think? Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:18",
      "text": "But Jesus knowing their wickedness, said: Why do you tempt me, ye hypocrites?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:19",
      "text": "Shew me the coin of the tribute. And they offered him a penny.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:20",
      "text": "And Jesus saith to them: Whose image and inscription is this?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:21",
      "text": "They say to him: Caesar's. Then he saith to them: Render therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar's; and to God, the things that are God's.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:22",
      "text": "And hearing this, they wondered and, leaving him, went their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:23",
      "text": "That day there came to him the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection; and asked him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:24",
      "text": "Saying: Master, Moses said: If a man die having no son, his brother shall marry his wife and raise up issue to his brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:25",
      "text": "Now there were with us seven brethren: and the first having married a wife, died; and not having issue, left his wife to his brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:26",
      "text": "In like manner the second and the third and so on, to the seventh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:27",
      "text": "And last of all the woman died also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:28",
      "text": "At the resurrection therefore, whose wife of the seven shall she be? For they all had her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:29",
      "text": "And Jesus answering, said to them: You err, not knowing the Scriptures nor the power of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:30",
      "text": "For in the resurrection they shall neither marry nor be married, but shall be as the angels of God in heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:31",
      "text": "And concerning the resurrection of the dead, have you not read that which was spoken by God, saying to you:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:32",
      "text": "I am the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob? He is not the God of the dead but of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:33",
      "text": "And the multitudes hearing it were in admiration at his doctrine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:34",
      "text": "But the Pharisees, hearing that he had silenced the Sadducees, came together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:35",
      "text": "And one of them, a doctor of the law, asked him, tempting him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:36",
      "text": "Master, which is the great commandment in the law?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:37",
      "text": "Jesus said to him: Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with thy whole heart and with thy whole soul and with thy whole mind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:38",
      "text": "This is the greatest and the first commandment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:39",
      "text": "And the second is like to this: Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:40",
      "text": "On these two commandments dependeth the whole law and the prophets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:41",
      "text": "And the Pharisees being gathered together, Jesus asked them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:42",
      "text": "Saying: What think you of Christ? Whose son is he? They say to him: David's.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:43",
      "text": "He saith to them: How then doth David in spirit call him Lord, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:44",
      "text": "The Lord said to my Lord: Sit on my right hand, until I make thy enemies thy footstool?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:45",
      "text": "If David then call him Lord, how is he his son?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:matthew.22.46",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:46",
      "text": "And no man was able to answer him a word: neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
